sentences: Joe Stubbs (born Joseph Stubbles; 1942 – February 5, 1998) was an American R&B/soul singer who became the lead singer of four different groups throughout his recording career.
Joe Stubbs was born six years after his brother Levi.
As a teenager, Stubbs joined the R&B group The Falcons in 1957 and led them on several of their early hits, among them the million-seller, "You're So Fine" (1959), and "The Teacher" (1960).
